<br>
 Assassins were a silent, hidden, and solitary bunch. When Dawn had left the camp to fight, to stalk, and to hunt the Roman soldiers the amazons were after, the solitary assassin mind set was all that she listened to.<br>
<br>
 When the intial fighting had taken place, Dawn had still seemed to be no where to be found. One would soon assume that what seemed to be a brave and strong assassin, had grown fearful and weak in her absence. <br>
<br>
 Of course. That was all contrary to the truth. The silent assassin was stronger than she had ever been, and hungry from tracking Roman soldiers for days, she found her battle closer to the village. . and the small amount of soldiers getting to Hippolyte and the others, was largely on her part, and her animal counter-parts.<br>
