It seemed that a lifetime had pasted since Hera had entered into Solari's mind. The last time the queen goddess had done so, Solari was protecting Hipployte and as a result of that, Hera possessed Solari's body.  <br>
Solari was extremely loyal and protective of Hippolyte. No one really knew the reason behind this, except those two and Hera. She flashed the vision of Hippolyte being taken by the roman soldier and the events that would follow. <br>
 &quot;Hera, you and I may have our differences, but I am at your command.&quot; Solari whispered to herself as her eyes flashed the peacock feather once more then vanished.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solariwolf@amazonsunite>solariwolf</A> at: 3/26/03 6:41:02 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=odessaofpaphos>Odessa of Paphos</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Amazon Queen</span><br>  Posts: 199<br> <font color=#993300>(3/26/03 6:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=115>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/xvmegvxwpt/images/amarice_11.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Battle changes</span><hr size=1> Odessa had returned to where Hippolyte had been fighting, and looked to the ground. She saw the footprints where he'd pushed her back, and followed into the forest where the two sets of prints had left, Dess blinked, and fell to her knees.<br>
