<br>
He carried Hippolyte inside and then tied her against a post.  Forcing her to stand, he tied her length to the post at several heights.  Still out, her body was limp, her head hanging forward.  <br>
<br>
&quot;This is the damned beast that attacked our village a few weeks ago.  She is only a woman.  And so are the other...'beasts'.  These damned Greeks and Trojans are weak fools to be fearful of them.&quot;  He called out to his comrads.<br>
<br>
Another spoke up, walking up to the Queen.  He grabbed her hair and pulled up so he could see her face.  Hippolyte moaned slightly, as the pull forced her out of her passed out state.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, we are Romans...not weaklings,&quot; said the one holding her head up.  &quot;We will take these women as new wives.  Besides,&quot; he chuckld.  &quot;I am getting tired of the ones I have.  Maybe these beast women will have enough spirit to handle me in bed.&quot;  He laughed harshly.<br>
<br>
Slowely, Hipolyte forced her eyes open.  Her body was in pain and her head was killing her.  But, she could see the men standing around her.  She must be in the Roman village.  Hipp forced her face to turn to stone, and her dark brown eyes gazed at the men.<br>
<br>
&quot;Aww...look, your new slave is awake,&quot; The man holding her hair pulled back hard, ramming the back of Hipp's head into the post and then let go.<br>
<br>
Hippolyte winced at the pain, but held her head up in dignity.<br>
<br>
Her captor looked her over and grinned, &quot;Well, slave....what is your name?&quot;<br>
<br>
Hippolyte said nothing.  She found herself to be tied to the post beyond any movement to free herself.   Her thoughts went to her athelfi in the woods.  Praying that they were safe.<br>
<br>
Her captor back hand struck her against the cheek.  &quot;What is your name, Slave?!&quot; He yelled at her in frustration.<br>
<br>
Again, Hippolyte said nothing. <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>

"We ride tonight!  With the strength that Hera has given
us-- and the strength that we have _earned_ for ourselves!  Take
what you need, but be quick.  Stay only until the sound of horn.
The moment you hear it-- we ride away.  Now-- to your horses."</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=solariwolf@amazonsunite>solariwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Themiscryian War Queen</span><br>  Posts: 149<br> <font color=#993300>(3/27/03 2:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=119>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: The Battle Changes</span><hr size=1> Solari groaned as she pulled herself to her feet. In pain and still a bit weak, she managed to grab her old clothing and place it on, depite it being blood soaked. She whistled for her horse to come to where she was. Her mare trotted over and knelt down for her master to mount up on. <br>
 &quot;Back to the others,my friend.&quot; Solari said weakly to her horse as she stood tall once more. The cry of her hawk and owl could be heard above her as they headed back to where the battle had taken place. <br>
Upon arriving back in the forest, the vision that was sent to her was confirmed by the looks on her fellow sisters' faces. She winced slightly as pain rumbled thru her body once more. The Romans' dagger did its damage well. But Solari ignored the pain and blood for the most part, knowing that it was once again time to plan for an attack. <br>
She dismounted her horse slowly, limping to where her broken sword laid. She bent down and picked it up, then looked around at her fellow sister's. <br>
&quot;We WILL get her back.&quot; She said softly. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=marpeamzn>Marpe Amzn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 64<br> <font color=#993300>(3/27/03 6:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1.topic&index=120>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.themiscrya.i-p.com/MarpeAmznrpg.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Making new friends</span><hr size=1> Marpe had fought hard and well, but not well enough she felt.  For one queen was badly injured and the other taken away.  It was a bad day for a guard of Themiscrya.  She stood near and waited as Solari was tended.  With Hippolyte gone, it was time for all to turn to the War Queen of Themiscrya.  As well, as the Vasilissa Alysia and Dawn.  Marpe was anxious but seasoned.  She knew to wait for orders.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showMessageRange?topicID=1.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showMessageRange?topicID=1.topic&start=21&stop=40>2</a><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showMessageRange?topicID=1.topic&start=41&stop=60>3</a><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showMessageRange?topicID=1.topic&start=61&stop=80>4</a><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showMessageRange?topicID=1.topic&start=81&stop=100>5</a> <b>6</b> <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showMessageRange?topicID=1.topic&start=121&stop=140>7</a><a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm66.showMess